k:prose-invert light\">\n<ol>\n<li>Good credit score.<\/li>\n<li>Clean driving record.<\/li>\n<li>Proof of income.<\/li>\n<li>Vehicle information.<\/li>\n<li>Personal information.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<div class=\"group w-full text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100 border-b border-black\/10 dark:border-gray-900\/50 dark:bg-gray-800\">\n<div class=\"flex p-4 gap-4 text-base md:gap-6 md:max-w-2xl lg:max-w-xl xl:max-w-3xl md:py-6 lg:px-0 m-auto\">\n<div class=\"relative flex flex-col w-[calc(100%-50px)] gap-1 md:gap-3 lg:w-[calc(100%-115px)]\">\n<div class=\"flex flex-grow flex-col gap-3\">\n<div class=\"group w-full text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100 border-b border-black\/10 dark:border-gray-900\/50 dark:bg-gray-800\">\n<div class=\"flex p-4 gap-4 text-base md:gap-6 md:max-w-2xl lg:max-w-xl xl:max-w-3xl md:py-6 lg:px-0 m-auto\">\n<div class=\"relative flex flex-col w-[calc(100%-50px)] gap-1 md:gap-3 lg:w-[calc(100%-115px)]\">\n<div class=\"flex flex-grow flex-col gap-3\">\n<h2 class=\"min-h-[20px] flex flex-col items-start gap-4 whitespace-pre-wrap break-words\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"How_do_I_Calculate_my_Payment_Premium\"><\/span>How do I Calculate my Payment Premium<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"group w-full text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100 border-b border-black\/10 dark:border-gray-900\/50 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-[#444654]\">\n<div class=\"flex p-4 gap-4 text-base md:gap-6 md:max-w-2xl lg:max-w-xl xl:max-w-3xl md:py-6 lg:px-0 m-auto\">\n<div class=\"flex-shrink-0 flex flex-col relative items-end\">\n<div class=\"text-xs flex items-center justify-center gap-1 invisible absolute left-0 top-2 -ml-4 -translate-x-full group-hover:visible !invisible\">To calculate your car insurance premium, insurance companies typically consider several factors such as:<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"relative flex flex-col w-[calc(100%-50px)] gap-1 md:gap-3 lg:w-[calc(100%-115px)]\">\n<div class=\"flex flex-grow flex-col gap-3\">\n<div class=\"min-h-[20px] flex flex-col items-start gap-4 whitespace-pre-wrap break-words\">\n<div class=\"markdown prose w-full break-words dark:prose-invert light\">\n<ol>\n<li>Age, gender, and marital status<\/li>\n<li>Driving record and history of accidents or traffic violations<\/li>\n<li>Type of vehicle, make and model, and age of the car<\/li>\n<li>Location and address where the car will be parked or stored<\/li>\n<li>Credit score and payment history<\/li>\n<li>Coverage limits and deductibles<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p>Based on these factors, the insurance company will assign a risk level to the driver and vehicle, and then calculate the premium accordingly. The premium may be paid in a lump sum, or in installments such as monthly, quarterly, or annually.<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/cars.usnews.com\/pics\/size\/350x262\/images\/Auto\/custom\/14928\/2022_Mercedes-AMG_GT_1.jpg\" alt=\"Affordable Auto Insurance Companies with Low Down Payments\" width=\"350\" height=\"262\" \/><\/p>\n<h2 id=\"cheap\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Affordable_Auto_Insurance_Companies_with_Low_Down_Payments\"><\/span>Affordable Auto Insurance Companies with Low Down Payments<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<table width=\"360\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"59%\"><strong>Insurance Companies<\/strong><\/td>\n<td width=\"40%\"><strong>Monthly Rate<\/strong><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"59%\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.valuepenguin.com\/state-farm-insurance-review\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">State Farm<\/a><\/td>\n<td width=\"40%\">$41<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"59%\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.valuepenguin.com\/geico-insurance-review\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Geico<\/a><\/td>\n<td width=\"40%\">$52<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"59%\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.valuepenguin.com\/american-family-insurance-review\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">American Family<\/a><\/td>\n<td width=\"40%\">$53<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"59%\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.valuepenguin.com\/progressive-insurance-review\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Progressive<\/a><\/td>\n<td width=\"40%\">$63<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"59%\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.valuepenguin.com\/travelers-insurance-review\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Travelers<\/a><\/td>\n<td width=\"40%\">$63<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"59%\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.valuepenguin.com\/nationwide-insurance-review\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Nationwide<\/a><\/td>\n<td width=\"40%\">$69<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"59%\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.valuepenguin.com\/allstate-auto-insurance-review\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Allstate<\/a><\/td>\n<td width=\"40%\">$79<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"59%\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.valuepenguin.com\/aaa-insurance-review\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">AAA<\/a><\/td>\n<td width=\"40%\">$87<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"59%\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.valuepenguin.com\/amica-insurance-review\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Amica<\/a><\/td>\n<td width=\"40%\">$92<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"59%\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.valuepenguin.com\/usaa-insurance-review\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">USAA*<\/a><\/td>\n<td width=\"40%\">$31<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<h2 id=\"afford\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"What_should_I_do_if_I_cant_afford_car_insurance_right_now\"><\/span>What should I do if I can&#8217;t afford car insurance right now?<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>If you are unable to afford car insurance but need to drive, there are a few options available to you. These include sharing a policy with others who drive your car, obtaining a non-owner policy, or opting for a liability-only policy.<\/p>\n<div class=\"ShortcodeList--root \">\n<div class=\"ShortcodeList--content ShortcodeList--content-margin\">\n<div class=\"ShortcodeList--column\">\n<ul class=\"ListUnordered--root ListUnordered--bullet\">\n<li class=\"ListUnordered--list-item\"><strong>Check your policy&#8217;s grace period.<\/strong>\u00a0If you can&#8217;t pay your car insurance bill right now but will have the money soon, ask your company about a\u00a0payment grace period. You could have a few days or weeks to come up with the money to keep your coverage.<\/li>\n<li class=\"ListUnordered--list-item\"><strong>Share a car insurance policy.<\/strong>\u00a0If you share a car with roommates or family members who live in the same home, you might be able to share a policy with them and split the cost. Or you could be added as a named driver to their policy.<\/li>\n<li class=\"ListUnordered--list-item\"><strong>Try a nonowner policy.<\/strong>\u00a0If you regularly drive someone else&#8217;s car, a\u00a0nonowner insurance policy\u00a0could help you get affordable coverage that&#8217;s up to 15% cheaper than a standard policy.<\/li>\n<li class=\"ListUnordered--list-item\"><strong>Drop to liability only.<\/strong>\u00a0Liability-only car insurance\u00a0is the cheapest coverage you can get, with an average cost of $58 per month nationwide.<\/li>\n<li class=\"ListUnordered--list-item\"><strong>Check for low-income savings.<\/strong>\u00a0Some states offer discounted car insurance policies for\u00a0drivers with low incomes, including California and New Jersey.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/form>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>If you&#8217;re looking for car insurance but don&#8217;t want to pay a down payment upfront, there are a few options available. You can start by comparing quotes from different insurance companies to find one that offers no down payment policies. What is No down Payment Car Insurance? No down payment car insurance is a type [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":10847,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[5],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/geetra.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/10844"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/geetra.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/geetra.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/geetra.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/geetra.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=10844"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/geetra.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/10844\/revisions"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/geetra.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/10847"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/geetra.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=10844"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/geetra.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=10844"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/geetra.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=10844"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}